a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes v w :: "real^2"
assumes h0 : "v = vector [3, 0]"
and h1 : "w = vector [2, -3]"
shows  "vector_projection v w = vector [12/13, -18/13]"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Find the projection of the vector $\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}$ onto the vector $\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix}.$ The final Answer is \begin{pmatrix} 12/13 \\ -18/13 \end{pmatrix}
 ### Proof
 From the formula for a projection, \[\operatorname{proj}_{\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix}}{\left\| \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix} \right\|^2} \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{6}{13} \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix} = \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} 12/13 \\ -18/13 \end{pmatrix}}.\]
 *)

theorem
fixes v w :: "real^2"
assumes h0 : "v = vector [3, 0]"
and h1 : "w = vector [2, -3]"
shows  "vector_projection v w = vector [12/13, -18/13]"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer

definition inner_product_2d :: "real*real ⇒ real*real ⇒ real" where  
"inner_product_2d v1 v2 = fst v1 * fst v2 + snd v1 * snd v2"  

theorem 
fixes a b projab :: "real*real" 
fixes cosab :: real
assumes h0 : "a = vector [3,0]"
and h1 : "b = vector [2,-3]"
and h2 : "cosab = (inner_product_2d a b) / sqrt ((inner_product_2d b b) * (inner_product_2d a a))"
and h3: "projab = vector [fst a * cosab^2, snd a * snd b* cosab^2 / fst b]"
shows "projab = vector [12/13,-18/13]"
